result.execSummary:
The defendant Clarence W Schick was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Imposed and Stayed.  4 days credit if revoked.

miscConds.notes: Plus supervision fees.    If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

No contact with:  any females under the age of 18 unless incidental or approved by Probation Agent; and D.D. and A.P.O. without Probation Agent's approval and victim's written consent.    Not to possess any firearms.  No computer use or devices without Probation Agent's approval.
Submit a DNA sample.  Defendant to comply with Sex Offender registry.

timeConds.notes:
Huber for work release; and treatment if qualifies.

Pursuant to Court Order dated 04/11/2018, defendant is to serve 45 days in Jail, with Huber privileges, to be served in Barron County Jail effective 03/28/2018.  
All other conditions remain in effect (see attached Order).
